In Posit Cloud (formerly known as RStudio Cloud), you can write your R code in an R Markdown (.Rmd) file or Quarto (.qmd) document to enable structured code execution and output, including captions and figure labels. Here’s a step-by-step guide to entering the code line by line, following the format provided.

Step-by-Step Instructions
Create a New R Markdown or Quarto Document:

Go to File > New File > R Markdown for an R Markdown file, or File > New File > Quarto Document for a Quarto file.
Choose a title for your document, and select either HTML or PDF as the output format.
Enter Code in Chunks:

In your .Rmd or .qmd file, create a new code chunk by clicking Insert > R (or pressing Ctrl+Alt+I).
Each code chunk starts with {r} (for R Markdown) or {r} or ```{r echo=FALSE} for Quarto.
Add Chunk Options:

Add the options for each chunk at the top of the chunk, after {r, as shown below. Here’s how each line should look in your code chunk.
Example:

markdown
复制代码
#| echo: false
#| warning: false
#| message: false
#| label: fig-trump-support-over-time
#| fig-cap: Trump's Support Percentage Over Time in U.S. Polls

trump_data <- read_csv("path/to/trump.csv")

# Convert date column to Date type if necessary
trump_data <- trump_data %>%
  mutate(end_date = as.Date(end_date, format="%Y-%m-%d"))

# Plot 1: Trump's Support Over Time
ggplot(trump_data, aes(x = end_date, y = pct)) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x = "Date",
       y = "Support Percentage",
       title = "Trump's Support Over Time") +
  theme_minimal()
